The paper focuses on a Human-Centric Cyber-Physical System and proposes a framework for occupant engagement-integration, which falls under the category of Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC). The paper also discusses the use of statistical learning algorithms for intelligent and autonomous incentive design, which falls under the categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the potential for improving sustainability and energy efficiency, which falls under the category of Cybernetics (cs.CY) and Smart Infrastructure (cs.SI).
